# API Configuration (REQUIRED - Replace with your actual values)
API_BASE_URL=https://your-api-server.com
APIKEY_MONGODB=your_api_key_here

# Training Configuration
EMBEDDING_MODEL=sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2
BATCH_SIZE=32
FETCH_BATCH_SIZE=100
SKIP_IF_NO_NEW_DATA=true

# Optional: Limit repos for testing
# MAX_REPOS=1000

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=INFO
# Training Pipeline - Docker Setup

This directory contains a fully containerized training pipeline that fetches repository data from your API and trains embedding models.

## Overview

**What it does:**
1. ✅ Fetches repository data from MongoDB API (remote server)
2. ✅ Trains embedding model using sentence-transformers
3. ✅ Saves trained model to persistent volume
4. ✅ Caches data locally for future runs
5. ✅ Only retrains when new data is available

**This is NOT the reranker** - this trains the initial embedding model that comes before the reranker in your pipeline.

## Quick Start

### 1. Create Environment File

Create `infrastructure/docker/.env`:

```bash
# API Configuration (REQUIRED - Replace with your actual values)
API_BASE_URL=https://your-api-server.com
APIKEY_MONGODB=your_api_key_here

# Training Configuration
EMBEDDING_MODEL=sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2
BATCH_SIZE=32
FETCH_BATCH_SIZE=100
SKIP_IF_NO_NEW_DATA=true

# Optional: Limit number of repos for testing
# MAX_REPOS=1000
```

### 2. Run Training (Simple)

From the project root:

```bash
cd infrastructure/docker
docker-compose -f docker-compose.training.yml up --build
```

### 3. Run Training (With Base Network)

If you need the web network:

```bash
cd infrastructure/docker
docker-compose -f docker-compose.base.yml -f docker-compose.training.yml up --build training
```

## What Happens

```
[Training Container Starts]
    ↓
[1] Fetch data from API
    • Connects to https://gitquery.davidhoerz.com
    • Downloads all repositories in batches
    • Caches to /app/training_data
    ↓
[2] Check for new data
    • Compares with last training run
    • Skips if no new repos (configurable)
    ↓
[3] Train embeddings
    • Uses sentence-transformers
    • GPU if available, CPU otherwise
    • Shows progress bar
    ↓
[4] Save model
    • Saves to /app/models/vectors/
    • Saves metadata to /app/models/metadata/
    • Creates "latest" symlinks
    ↓
[5] Exit
    • Container stops (restart: "no")
    • Models persist in Docker volume
```

## Accessing Trained Models

### View Models in Volume

```bash
# List volumes
docker volume ls | grep training

# Inspect models
docker run --rm -v git-query-training-models:/models alpine ls -lah /models/vectors
docker run --rm -v git-query-training-models:/models alpine ls -lah /models/metadata
```

### Copy Models to Host

```bash
# Copy entire models directory
docker run --rm -v git-query-training-models:/models -v ${PWD}:/backup alpine cp -r /models /backup/trained_models

# Or copy specific files
docker run --rm -v git-query-training-models:/models -v ${PWD}:/backup alpine cp /models/vectors/repo_embeddings_latest.npy /backup/
```

### Mount Models in Recommender Service

Update `docker-compose.reco.yml`:

```yaml
services:
  recommender:
    volumes:
      - training-models:/app/models:ro  # Read-only mount

volumes:
  training-models:
    name: git-query-training-models
    external: true
```

## Configuration Options

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `API_BASE_URL` | `https://gitquery.davidhoerz.com` | Your API server URL |
| `APIKEY_MONGODB` | `apikey` | MongoDB API key |
| `EMBEDDING_MODEL` | `sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` | Model to use |
| `BATCH_SIZE` | `32` | Embedding batch size |
| `FETCH_BATCH_SIZE` | `100` | API fetch batch size |
| `MAX_REPOS` | (none) | Limit repos for testing |
| `SKIP_IF_NO_NEW_DATA` | `true` | Skip training if no new data |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | `INFO` | Logging level |

### Model Options

**Fast & Small (Default):**
```bash
EMBEDDING_MODEL=sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2
# 384 dimensions, ~80MB, very fast
```

**Better Quality:**
```bash
EMBEDDING_MODEL=sentence-transformers/all-mpnet-base-v2
# 768 dimensions, ~420MB, slower but better
```

**Multilingual:**
```bash
EMBEDDING_MODEL=sentence-transformers/paraphrase-multilingual-mpnet-base-v2
# 768 dimensions, supports 50+ languages
```

## Running on Different Hardware

### Run on Another Machine

1. **Copy the repo** to the target machine
2. **Create `.env`** with your API credentials
3. **Run the container**:

```bash
docker-compose -f docker-compose.training.yml up --build
```

4. **Copy trained models back** (optional):

```bash
# On training machine
docker run --rm -v git-query-training-models:/models -v ${PWD}:/backup alpine tar czf /backup/models.tar.gz -C /models .

# Transfer models.tar.gz to your server

# On server
tar xzf models.tar.gz -C /path/to/models/
```

### GPU Support

The container automatically uses GPU if available (CUDA).

**For GPU training:**

1. Install [nvidia-docker](https://github.com/NVIDIA/nvidia-docker)

2. Update `docker-compose.training.yml`:

```yaml
services:
  training:
    deploy:
      resources:
        reservations:
          devices:
            - driver: nvidia
              count: 1
              capabilities: [gpu]
```

3. Run normally - will use GPU automatically

## Scheduled Training

### Using Cron

Run training daily at 2 AM:

```bash
0 2 * * * cd /path/to/git-query/infrastructure/docker && docker-compose -f docker-compose.training.yml up --build >> /var/log/training.log 2>&1
```

### Using systemd Timer

Create `/etc/systemd/system/git-query-training.service`:

```ini
[Unit]
Description=Git-Query Training Pipeline
After=docker.service
Requires=docker.service

[Service]
Type=oneshot
WorkingDirectory=/path/to/git-query/infrastructure/docker
ExecStart=/usr/bin/docker-compose -f docker-compose.training.yml up --build
StandardOutput=journal
StandardError=journal

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

Create `/etc/systemd/system/git-query-training.timer`:

```ini
[Unit]
Description=Run Git-Query Training Daily
Requires=git-query-training.service

[Timer]
OnCalendar=daily
Persistent=true

[Install]
WantedBy=timers.target
```

Enable:

```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable git-query-training.timer
sudo systemctl start git-query-training.timer
```

## Monitoring

### View Logs

```bash
# Follow logs in real-time
docker-compose -f docker-compose.training.yml logs -f training

# View last run
docker logs git-query-training
```

### Check Training Status

```bash
# Check if model exists
docker run --rm -v git-query-training-models:/models alpine cat /models/metadata/training_metadata_latest.json

# View training summary
docker run --rm -v git-query-training-models:/models alpine cat /models/metadata/training_metadata_latest.json | jq .
```

## Troubleshooting

### Container exits immediately

Check logs:
```bash
docker logs git-query-training
```

Common issues:
- API credentials wrong
- Network not created (run base compose first)
- Server unreachable

### No new data message

If `SKIP_IF_NO_NEW_DATA=true` and no new repos since last run:
```
⏭ Skipping training - no new data
```

Force retraining:
```bash
SKIP_IF_NO_NEW_DATA=false docker-compose -f docker-compose.training.yml up
```

### Out of memory

Reduce batch size:
```bash
BATCH_SIZE=16 docker-compose -f docker-compose.training.yml up
```

### Slow download

Reduce fetch batch size:
```bash
FETCH_BATCH_SIZE=50 docker-compose -f docker-compose.training.yml up
```

## Output Structure

```
/app/models/
├── vectors/
│   ├── repo_embeddings_latest.npy          # Latest embeddings
│   └── repo_embeddings_20260216_143000.npy # Timestamped backup
├── metadata/
│   ├── repo_mapping_latest.json            # Repo ID -> index mapping
│   ├── training_metadata_latest.json       # Training config & stats
│   └── ...
└── checkpoints/                            # (cleaned up after success)

/app/training_data/
├── repositories_latest.json                # Latest fetched data
└── repositories_20260216_143000.json       # Timestamped backup
```

## Integration with Recommender

To use trained models in your recommender service:

1. **Share volume** between training and recommender containers
2. **Load embeddings** in recommender startup:

```python
import numpy as np

embeddings = np.load('/app/models/vectors/repo_embeddings_latest.npy')
with open('/app/models/metadata/repo_mapping_latest.json') as f:
    mapping = json.load(f)
```

## Advanced Usage

### Test with Limited Data

```bash
MAX_REPOS=100 docker-compose -f docker-compose.training.yml up --build
```

### Force Retrain

```bash
# Remove metadata to force fresh training
docker run --rm -v git-query-training-models:/models alpine rm -f /models/metadata/training_metadata_latest.json

# Run training
docker-compose -f docker-compose.training.yml up
```

### Clean Everything

```bash
# Stop and remove container
docker-compose -f docker-compose.training.yml down

# Remove volumes (WARNING: deletes all trained models!)
docker volume rm git-query-training-models git-query-training-data git-query-training-logs
```

## Performance

**Typical performance** (all-MiniLM-L6-v2, CPU):
- Fetch: ~200-500 repos/sec (depends on network)
- Train: ~50-100 repos/sec (CPU), ~500-1000 repos/sec (GPU)
- Total for 10k repos: ~5-10 minutes (CPU), ~2-3 minutes (GPU)

